cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper is about training a statistical spoken dialogue system (SDS) using neural networks to rate the success of a dialogue without any prior knowledge of the user's task. This involves reinforcement learning in SDS. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. The paper also deals with spoken dialogue systems, which suggests cs.SD (Sound) as a possible category. The use of neural networks for reinforcement learning suggests cs.LG (Learning) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with user feedback and monitoring a dialogue, which suggests cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as a possible category.
